# Cloudflare Pages — explicit routing rules
# Generated: 2026-04-27
# Purpose: override the default SPA fallback so /docs.html, /docs/*, and
# /docs-assets/* are served as their actual files (not rewritten to /index.html).
#
# Without this file, Pages was returning index.html for every URL that did not
# match its initial deploy snapshot, breaking the documentation viewer.
#
# Rules are evaluated top-to-bottom; first match wins. The `!` flag forces
# the rule to take precedence over Pages' built-in SPA fallback.

# ── Documentation viewer (must take precedence) ────────────────────────
/docs.html               /docs.html                       200!
/docs                    /docs.html                       200!
/docs/                   /docs.html                       200!

# ── Markdown source files (fetched by viewer.js) ──────────────────────
/docs/:slug.md           /docs/:slug.md                   200!

# ── Static assets (CSS, JS, JSON, interactive chart) ──────────────────
/docs-assets/:asset      /docs-assets/:asset              200!
/docs-assets/:asset.html /docs-assets/:asset.html         200!

# ── Existing site root + landing fallback ─────────────────────────────
# (No SPA fallback declared — Pages will 404 missing assets, which is
#  the desired behaviour. If a true SPA fallback is needed later, add:
#    /*                  /index.html                       200
#  but ONLY after the rules above so they win precedence.)
